body:
@VBelozyorov @junichi11 

This is IMHO not needed, even not recommended since the changes will be lost on PHP sigfiles update.

Simply put your files to **any** folder and add this folder to the PHP Include Path - either in Tools > Options for global availability or in the Project Properties dialog if you want these files to be available only in the given project.

@ebarboni yes, be good to get this in - finding it a bit of a usability issue on a high resolution screen.

+0 to the approach - right for 11.3, but I think we need a concerted effort to get rid of these isXxxxLaF patterns in 12.0

Aside - @ebarboni why is the milestone marked closed already?  Makes it harder to mark PRs for your review for this release.

@pedro-w thanks for the screenshots with different LAFs, much appreciated.

The Heap View looks certainly better, it is crisper and more readable.

I am not a committer and cannot approve the PR but the changes look good to me.

Will merge.
@blackleg would be good for 5.X to have a workaround saying how to modify config file to get it work
